A few of my most exciting and amazing memories from this year. Not because this year was that amazing for me but because despite all that was going on I still chose to see the best in it✨ 

1. Started 2021 in Dominican republic. Not because we planned but because all of our plans failed and this is where we ended up. And that’s when I began to embrance failure already in January hehe #cheers!
2. Went home and spend quality time with my friends. Nothing can compare.
3. Traveled across the globe from NY to Maldives for 2 and half days shoot. I love what I do so much I even stop being jet lagged lol
4. I celebrated my birthday in Rio. Nothing will ever beat this time. I flew from NY and my boyfriend from Europe. This was one of the most exciting trips this year and in this life.
5. Also I traveled to Italy for some campaign shoot. To the mountins. To the snow. In May (I was doubting that I love what I do🥶and that’s when I realize that the colder the weather the less I like my job)
6. Was honoured to shoot in this photographers villa in Corsica. He got it in his 50ies. So I still have plenty of time🥹
7. Watching the most amazing sunset in Ibiza. I could do this every day of my life and never get bored.
8. Worked in Amsterdam where lives my cousin. I had an extra day before my other travel and we had the best time ever.
9. I took my mum and brother to Mallorca. There’s nothing like taking time off to spend with them♥️
10. 34 degrees in Paris and we shot coats. For 2 days🥹or you’re freezing or you’re boiling there’s no in between in modeling.
